5:
The Swallow Knights? Is this some
kind of joke?
9:
As free knights, we will fight to
protect the kingdom of our own
accord.
11:
As we belong to no House, we can
be helped by whomever deigns to
do so, be it Nouin or Tris, without
being indebted to any party.
14:
That is how it would work in theory,
yes.
17:
You say knights, plural, but you are
alone.
20:
I will enlist help from Palpebra's
adventurers and others from lands
even farther away than that. Surely
no one will object to me calling
upon friends for aid.
24:
An interesting proposal, but those
who oppose Palpebra's interference
won't be convinced.
28:
But having pretext alone is good
enough, isn't it?
33:
Very well. House Tris promises to
help the Swallow Knights.
41:
I have already done all the
convincing necessary.
46:
Thank you for taking the time to see
me, Ignatz.
48:
I apologize for taking so long to
come back—
51:
I hear you've become a pawn for the
Sweses.
54:
And now, what is this about the
Swallow Knights? You plan to make
the same mistake twice?
57:
I will deal with House Swes and
Palpebra. You need only fulfill your
duty as a Nouin.
62:
P-please, Ignatz. Wait. This has
nothing to do with House Swes!
Yuwel came up with the idea of his
own volition!
67:
It's all right, Your Highness. I can
handle this.
70:
I have connections in Palpebra that
the rest of House Nouin does not. I
should be the one talking to them.
74:
Azrail will worry about that. There is
no need for you to utter a single
word.
78:
Have you forgotten your relationship
with House Tris? They won't stand
idly by if Palpebra—
81:
Enough. Do not tire your little head
with politics. That is my
responsibility.
84:
I have been telling you this for a
long, long time. Do not repeat your
mistakes from before.
88: I see you haven't changed a bit.
91:
I am here with His Highness to
propose an alliance with House
Swes. I am not here as the third son
of House Nouin. That man died five
years ago.
94:
As things stand, your soldiers will
soon succumb to exhaustion. Why
persist in this course of action?
101: You... are not the Yuwel I once knew.
105:
I've been through a lot. But we have
more important matters to discuss.
112:
I see. It seems that my concern was
unwarranted.
116:
Excuse me, Cieldeau. I have a few
questions for you too.
118:
Which soldiers will you send into this
battle?
128:
Truthfully, I would prefer not to ask
you this! But...
131:
Are you not worried your army
might be seen as inferior to those of
both House Nouin and Palpebra?
140:
Understood, Your Highness. I will
take this provocation in earnest.
142:
My personal elite troops shall take
the stage in the coming battle. Is
that satisfactory?
152:
In return, I expect your connections
to be as useful as you boast, Yuwel.
160:
I... or rather, a friend of mine has
more influence than you could ever
imagine.
165:
I'll continue facilitating negotiations
with the academy. Please take care
of the Farlands in my stead.
168:
You can count on us. Does this
mean our first wave of
reinforcements is ready?
177:
...Nope. Not happening, Mister Prince.
We already discussed this.
186:
As you may already know, the King
has approved the re-establishment
of the Swallow Knights.
190:
Thank you, House Tris. House Nouin.
The Sweses and Sextans alone
could not have done this.
194:
It is too soon for your gratitude.
Danger lingers in our lands, and the
Kweturs continue to be contrarian.
199:
Indeed. Unfortunately, to appease
them, we had to make the Swallow
Knights a temporary organization.
One to be disbanded when this is
over.
202:
However, there are now many,
including the three Houses present,
fighting in unison for a single cause.
204:
Despite everything, I'm proud to see
us come together.
207:
And now, it is time to officially
appoint our captain of the Swallow
Knights! Yuwel, if you wouldn't mind!
213:
Yuwel Nouin. I dub thee Captain of
the Swallow Knights!
221:
A step forward... A small one,
blessed by less than half of the Nine
Houses.
224: But it is a first step nonetheless.
229:
Let us be off, Yuwel! We will start by
rescuing the people!
